  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2007-07-26",
    "date": "2007-08-31T20:16:39Z",
    "text": "Grants immunity from civil liability to: (1) persons who, in good faith and based on an objectively reasonable suspicion, report suspicious activity involving or directed against a passenger transportation system, a threat to such system or to passenger safety or security, or an act of terrorism; and (2) passenger transportation security system employees or agents and other federal employees with transportation security responsibilities who take reasonable actions, in good faith, to respond to reported threats."
